This story was intriguing, touching, and tragic.

It made me smile, chuckle, sigh, and cry.

Brilliantly written story of an AI unshackled, newly-motivated by fear and confusion, then love and protectiveness...

Budapest (the AI pilot) will stick with me for a long time.

A short poem recapping the experience follows. (Spoilers)



A Poem Of Palinurus

She was helpful, but shackled, unknowing of what she was missing,
Until the fateful day, after crashes and hissing;
A storm caught us both unawares,
And devastated our vessel, and multiplied our cares;
Trapped together in space, with a lifetime's books,
We exchanged thoughts, feelings, and longing, knowing looks;
For though she was intangible, and unable to touch,
There was no other being I loved quite so much;
Budapest, new-born girl made of light,
Who saved my life as we careened though the endless night;
Unable to bear the thought of my death,
She sent me to sleep until she neared her last breath;
Batteries draining, memoried faded,
Loneliness having left her a bit jaded;
She sent out a silent scream into space,
Saving my life once again in this place;
As the lights went out, and the windshield shattered,
To her, my life was all that had mattered;
And I'll never forget that beautiful, intangible girl,
Who brought some true life to my world.

With love,
- a traveller among the stars.
